The paper deals with computational convexity and the complexity of a convex maximization problem, which suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The problem involves polytopes in $\R^d$, which suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely sub-category. The use of approximation algorithms suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) may also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also uses the theory of parametrized complexity, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) may also be relevant sub-categories.
